---
import Article from '../../../layouts/Article.astro';
import Fig from '../../../components/Fig.astro';
import Callout from '../../../components/Callout.astro';
import DataTable from '../../../components/DataTable.astro';
import FaqBlock from '../../../components/FaqBlock.astro';
import CtaButton from '../../../components/CtaButton.astro';
import { getRebates } from '../../../lib/data';
import { formatAud, formatDateLong } from '../../../lib/rebate';

const rebates = getRebates();
const typicalInstalled = 6500;
const panelKw = 6.6;
const zoneRating = 1.382;
const deemingYears = 2030 - 2026;
const stcPrice = rebates.stcPrice.netAssumed;
const panelStcs = Math.floor(panelKw * zoneRating * deemingYears);
const panelRebate = panelStcs * stcPrice;
const net = typicalInstalled - panelRebate;

const faq = [
  {
    question: 'Is 6.6 kW still a sensible default?',
    answer:
      'It remains a common single-phase sweet spot, but many homes now quote 8–10 kW if the switchboard and export limits allow. Match array size to daytime load and roof — not to a 2018 rule of thumb.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does this include a battery?',
    answer:
      'No. This page is panels-only. For combined packages see the Perth solar + battery page; battery support uses the separate Cheaper Home Batteries Program.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Why is my STC discount different?',
    answer:
      'Zone rating, exact deeming factor, and certificate price on the day all move. Our example is illustrative using the same net STC assumption as our battery maths.',
  },
];

const description = `Typical 6.6 kW rooftop solar cost in Australia after STC discount. Planning installed about ${formatAud(typicalInstalled)}; worked STC example included.`;
---

<Article
  title="6.6 kW solar system cost (after STCs)"
  description={description}
  crumbs={[
    { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { label: 'Costs', href: '/costs/6-6kw-solar-system-cost/' },
    { label: '6.6 kW solar' },
  ]}
  updated="2026-07-12"
  verified={rebates.meta.lastVerified}
>
  <Fragment slot="toc">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#price">Typical price</a></li>
      <li><a href="#stc">STC discount</a></li>
      <li><a href="#drivers">What moves quotes</a></li>
      <li><a href="#battery">Adding a battery</a></li>
      <li><a href="#sources">Sources</a></li>
    </ul>
  </Fragment>

  <p>
    A <Fig>{panelKw}</Fig> kW rooftop system is still the yardstick many Australian quotes use. Panel and
    inverter prices have fallen for years, while the STC deeming period keeps shrinking toward{' '}
    <Fig>2030</Fig> — so net cost is a race between hardware deflation and fewer certificates. Verified
    data stamp on related rebate files: {formatDateLong(rebates.meta.lastVerified)}.
  </p>

  <h2 id="price">Typical installed price</h2>
  <p>
    Our planning mid-point for a straightforward <Fig>{panelKw}</Fig> kW install is about{' '}
    <Fig>{formatAud(typicalInstalled)}</Fig> before STCs. Tier-one hardware, tile roofs, and long DC runs
    sit higher; bare promotional “from” prices sit lower and often exclude extras.
  </p>

  <h2 id="stc">Illustrative STC discount</h2>
  <DataTable
    caption="Zone-3 style example — replace with CER figures on your quote"
    headers={['Line', 'Value']}
    rows={[
      ['Typical installed', formatAud(typicalInstalled)],
      ['STCs (floored)', String(panelStcs)],
      ['Assumed net $/STC', formatAud(stcPrice)],
      ['Illustrative STC discount', formatAud(panelRebate)],
      ['Illustrative net', formatAud(net)],
    ]}
    numericCols={[1]}
  />
  <p>
    More detail on zones and deeming: <a href="/solar-rebate/">solar panel rebate (STCs)</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="drivers">What drives quotes up or down</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Panel tier and inverter brand / hybrid readiness</li>
    <li>Roof type, storeys, and split arrays</li>
    <li>Export limits and meter upgrades</li>
    <li>Council or strata constraints</li>
    <li>Whether an electrician must upgrade the main switchboard</li>
  </ul>
  <Callout type="note" title="No installer picks in v1">
    <p>We publish cost bands and rebate maths — not a recommended installer list.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="battery">Adding a battery later or together</h2>
  <p>
    Hybrid inverters cost more upfront but simplify a later battery. If you are buying both now, demand
    separate STC (panels) and Cheaper Home Batteries (battery) lines. Start with{' '}
    <a href="/costs/13-5kwh-battery-cost/">13.5 kWh battery cost</a> or the{' '}
    <a href="/costs/solar-battery-package-perth/">Perth package page</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    <CtaButton href="/solar-rebate/">Read the STC guide</CtaButton>
  </p>

  <h2 id="sources">Sources</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.cleanenergyregulator.gov.au/">Clean Energy Regulator</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/feed-in-tariffs/">Feed-in tariffs</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <FaqBlock items={faq} />
</Article>
